The paper focuses on using deep convolutional neural networks for detecting abnormalities in mammogram images, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of deep learning algorithms also suggests the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The paper specifically deals with mammogram images, which falls under the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the use of neural networks for classification and localization suggests the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
